    "• DNS -a Universal Key Name Service -can bind the provider's public key to the interest.",
    "• A worldwide search service, for instance, Google.",
    "For the elimination of the overhead, the authors divide the propose work into edge routers and core routers.",
    "The IKB check can be performed through edge routers, while the subset of content packets can be verified randomly through core routers, as shown in Fig. 14.",
    "However, the proposed mechanism is not scalable and completely based on the concept of public key infrastructure (PKI) which makes it hard to verify the signature at line speed."
